\par 
\par In the COM profile, an implementation that fails to perform an interface method can retu
rn a HRESULT value of E_FAIL.  Successful method functions will return S_OK.  In most COM client environments (e.g. Visual Basic and ATL C++) these return codes are processed by client-side stub code, and errors are converted into exceptions that the clie
nt application must catch.  C client programmers should check all the HRESULT return values with the SUCCEEDED macro.
\par 
\par In the Java profile, an implementation that fails to perform an interface method should throw a runtime exception.
\par 
\par No exceptions have been specified in the CORBA profile.
\par 
\par {\*\bkmkstart _Toc496925552}{\listtext\pard\plain\s2 \b \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 3.5\tab}}\pard\plain \s2\ql \fi-864\li864\ri0\sb120\sa120\keepn\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx864\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls3\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin864\itap0 
