\par External authorities may be used to manage definitions of objects used in this Interface Specification.  The definitions of these objects are referenced using code strings.  The codes and authority names can be embedded in WKT strings or XML
, using an AUTHORITY clause.
\par 
\par If there is an AUTHORITY clause, and the reader recognizes the authority name, then the reader is entitled to use the authority\rquote s definition, and ignore all the other values at that level in the definition.  (How the reader co
nsults the authority is outside the scope of this Interface Specification.)
\par 
\par To improve interoperability, writers of WKT and XML must always include a copy of all the values, as well as any AUTHORITY clause.
\par 
\par Readers will use the values (as opposed to the authority code) in the following cases:
\par 
