Some of the interfaces specified in this document have methods for returning the XML definition of the object.  In addition, some of the \lquote factory\rquote  interfaces have methods for creating a new object from an XML definition.  These
 methods have been left in the interfaces in anticipation of a future \lquote normative\rquote  specification.  It is recommended that implementations of this version of the specification use this XML definition.
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par For all entities that can be printed in WKT format, there is a corresponding encoding in XML format.
\par 
\par The benefit of WKT is that it already exists as part of the Simple Features specification, it has been proved to work in practice, it has already been released in commercial products, and OGC retains control over its development.
\par 
\par The benefit of XML is that there are widely available software tools for creating, parsing and processing it.  OGC does not have so much control over its development.
\par  
\par Both formats will be mandatory for all entity interfaces that have exporting methods using these formats, and all factory interfaces that have creation methods using these formats.
\par 
